<h1 id="about-pearls-of-india">About pearls of India</h1>
<p>Here we have another game using the cascading reels feature. As such Pearls of India plays using five reels and 20 bet lines. Where this game really shines is the free spin rounds where the multipliers can reach as high as x50. The game also has bonus games. Activating the bonus game allows you choose between three temples. In these temples there are different bonus games called Statue of Vishnu, Wheel of Brahma and Wall of Shiva.</p>
<h2 id="game-features">Game Features</h2>
<p>The first feature we’re seeing in Pearls of India is the Cascading Reels feature, making symbols fall down, replacing any winning symbols and triggering a re-spin on every win. These re-spins are also activating multipliers allowing for big wins when you string together chains of consecutive wins. Added to the cascading reels the slot also has free spins and the three bonus games.</p>
<h3 id="cascading-reels">Cascading Reels</h3>
<p>Winning symbols are removed and new symbols cascade down from above, replacing them and creating new combinations in Pearls of India. When this happens the slot applies a multiplier to all wins. The multiplier is x1 round one increasing to x2, x4, x6 and finally x10 in the following rounds.</p>
<h3 id="free-spin-feature">Free Spin Feature</h3>
<p>Activating the Free Spin feature requires three pearl symbols. Once triggered you’re getting ten free spins with the possibility of winning even more by collecting additional pearls. Collecting five pearls during free spins gives you five additional free spins and increases your multiplier.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>5 Pearls</strong>
<ul>
<li>TheMultiplier values are 2x, 4x, 8x, 12x &amp; 20x along with 5 extra free spins</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>10 Pearls</strong>
<ul>
<li>Multiplier values are 3x, 6x, 12x, 18x and 30x along with 5 extra free spins</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>15 Pearls</strong>
<ul>
<li>Multiplier values are 4x, 8x, 16x, 24x and 40x along with 5 extra free spins</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>20 Pearls</strong>
<ul>
<li>Multiplier values are 5x, 10x, 20x, 30x and 50x along with 5 extra free spins</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="bonus-rounds">Bonus Rounds</h3>
<p>Starting the bonus rounds in Pearls of India requires you to collect 25 temple symbols. Once you’re done collecting those you’re facing the choice of which bonus game you want. The bonus games you’re choosing from are called Wall of Shiva, Statue of Vishnu and Wheel of Brahma.</p>
<h4 id="statue-of-vishnu">Statue of Vishnu</h4>
<p>In this temple you’re facing a statue of Vishnu. En each of the statues hand it’s holding a pearl and one is resting on it’s head. In this bonus game you’re choosing pearls to gain prizes.</p>
<h4 id="wheel-of-brahma">Wheel of Brahma</h4>
<p>The second temple presents the player with a rotating, circular puzzle containing three rings. The goal in this bonus game is matching the shapes of the puzzle, more matches gives higher winnings.</p>
<h4 id="wall-of-shiva">Wall of Shiva</h4>
<p>In this temple you’re facing a wall with 5x5 tiles. You have to select tiles to win prizes, ending the game whenever a “dangerous animal” tile is selected.</p>
